{"questionId":"19427","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows a water wheel with centre <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>O</mtext></math> and radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> metres. Water flows&nbsp;into buckets, turning the wheel clockwise at a constant speed.</p>\n<p><br>The height, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> metres, of the top of a bucket above the ground <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds after it passes&nbsp;through point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math> is modelled by the function</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>18</mn></mfrac><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>18</mn></mfrac><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>, for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/114b7281e3843305f24bc48f918ad2e37c400001.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A bucket moves around to point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math> which is at a height of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn></math> metres above the ground.&nbsp;It takes&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> seconds for the top of this bucket to go from point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math> to point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The chord&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>[</mo><mtext>AB</mtext><mo>]</mo></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>17</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn></math> metres, correct to three significant figures.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the rate of change of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> when the top of the bucket is at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognizing rate of change is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>'</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>eg&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>k</mi></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>11</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6510</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>782024</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>782024</mn></math>&nbsp; (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>768662</mn></math>&nbsp;from&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>sf</mtext></math> )</p>\n<p>rate of change is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>782</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><msup><mtext>ms</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp; &nbsp;N2</strong></em></p>\n<p>(<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>769</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><msup><mtext>ms</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mfenced></math>&nbsp;from&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>sf</mtext></math> )</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19427","referenceCode":"20N.2.SL.TZ0.S_8d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Determine the rate of change of h when the top of the bucket is at B.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.9—HL modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}